M||titl|rc 19 ap Changes
M||impa|md
M||impa|cleaner cp definitions and context usage
M||tags|react19, refs, context, hooks
M||tx|---
M|Reac|tx|> **⚠️ rc 19+ only.** Skip this if you're on rc 18 or earlier.
M|Reac|tx|In rc 19, `ref` is now a regular prop (no `forwardRef` wrapper needed), and `use()` replaces `useContext()`.
M|Reac|**In|**
M|Reac|tx|```tsx
M|Reac|tx|const ComposerInput = forwardRef<TextInput, Props>((props, ref) => {
M|Reac|tx|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|Reac|tx|})
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**Co|**
M|Reac|tx|```tsx
M|Reac|func|Props & { ref?: rc.Ref<TextInput> }) {
M|Reac|tx|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|Reac|tx|}
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**In|**
M|Reac|tx|```tsx
M|Reac|tx|const value = useContext(MyContext)
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**Co|**
M|Reac|tx|```tsx
M|Reac|tx|const value = use(MyContext)
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|tx|`use()` can also be called conditionally, unlike `useContext()`.